    CLIMATE SCIENCE OLYMPIAD 2022 - School Qualifying Round

    by Mary Joy Villamora - Wednesday, 30 March 2022, 11:48 AM

    The student competition to find solutions to climate change. Open to all interested G10 and G11 scholars.

    1. How It Works

      2. School Qualifying Round

      A 25-minute online quiz will be done in sync for all interested G10 - G11 scholars on May 6, 2022 at 10:00 AM and will serve as a qualifying round at PSHS-CVisC Level.  Each person can participate up to 3 times. All participants will receive a certificate. 

      In preparation for this round, the interested participants will be given access to Climate Science Courses and activities.  and Before the actual test, a mock exam using the CS Quiz app will be conducted.

      3. Quarter Finals (Best 10% globally)

      The best 10% of all qualifier attempts advance to the Quarter Finals. Quarter Finals follow the same quick-question format as Qualifying Round (25-minute online quiz).

      4. Semi-Finals

      In the Semi-Finals, the partcipants choose one of three problem statements to respond to. To help them prepare, the partcipants are told the topics 10 days before the event, but the exact problem statement is only revealed at the start of the actual qualifier event. Then they have 3 hours to research and write essay responses to questions related to the problem statement. ClimateScience.org will score each team's solution.

      5. Finals (Top 100 globally)

      Every finalist will be awarded a Bronze Medal, the top 20 and top 10 will be awarded a Silver and Gold Medal, respectively. The top teams split the prize pool of $15,000 (USD). In the finals, you'll write a proposal about a major climate-related issue and be interviewed by our judges. As in 2021, we hope to conduct the winners ceremony at the United Nations' Climate Summit (COP) and give the top teams the opportunity to present their solutions on a world stage.


      IF YOU ARE INTERESTED TO JOIN, PLEASE CONTACT ME AT mmvillamora@cvisc.pshs.edu.ph ON OR BEFORE APRIL 18, 2022. 

      Thank you!
